<br>
Now a mage or melee will take argo without even attacking, but pet will hold good argo as long as all are outside melee range. <br>
<br>
For an all mage trials group you will need each pet to take one mob, and even in the worst case situation of 4 lizard guys you can move through them very easy. If you have it cast the 45 DS on the pets. The mobs have about 10k hp so if each mage casted 2 times per mob they would go down like flies, and leave very little chance for argo.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you can banish one then you really only need to cast heavy on 2 mobs where the last will be most likely 1/2 life with 6 pets on it by the time you get to it.<br>
<br>
I did a 4 mage 1 wiz 1 cleric and we all had 70m on last mob and chain pets on it using zero DDs. No one casted a pet more then 2 times. <br>
<br>
Aego the pets too.<br>
